&lt;p id="ZMaEwH"&gt;At $279.99, the fourth generation of the Nest Learning Thermostat is more expensive than &lt;a href="https://www.anrdoezrs.net/links/8532386/type/dlg/sid/verge/https://store.google.com/product/nest_learning_thermostat_3rd_gen?hl=en-US" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;the third-gen Nest&lt;/a&gt;, which launched in 2015. However, it now comes with a new &lt;a href="https://www.anrdoezrs.net/links/8532386/type/dlg/sid/verge/https://store.google.com/us/product/nest_temperature_sensor_2nd_gen?hl=en-US&amp;amp;selections=eyJwcm9kdWN0RmFtaWx5IjoiWkdWMmFXTmxYMlpoYldsc2VWOWZibVZ6ZEY5MFpXMXdYM05sYm5OdmNsOHlibVJmWjJWdVgyWmhiUT09In0%3D" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;Nest Temperature Sensor (2nd gen)&lt;/a&gt; to monitor temperature in other rooms. Both are available for preorder now and will ship on August 20th — in the US and Canada only. &lt;/p&gt;
